    <briefdescription>
<para>DNS Service Discovery record. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This structure used in the implementation of RFC 6763 and should not need to be accessed directly from application code.</para>
<para>The <emphasis>port</emphasis> pointer must be non-NULL. When the value in <emphasis>port</emphasis> is non-zero, the service is advertised as being on that particular port. When the value in <emphasis>port</emphasis> is zero, then the service is not advertised.</para>
<para>Thus, it is possible for multiple services to advertise on a particular port if they hard-code the port.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="see"><para><ulink url="https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6763">RFC 6763</ulink> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
